definitions.definition: A building for keeping goods of any kind, especially provisions.
A single location or resource where a large quantity of something can be found.
examples: This old book is a genuine storehouse of useful cooking tips.

definitions.definition: A mass or quantity laid up.

main_definition: A building for keeping goods of any kind, especially provisions.
secondary_definitions: ( figurative , by extension ) A single location or resource where a large quantity of something can be found.
( obsolete ) A mass or quantity laid up.
